Set the time. Intended to be used this way to set the time: (perl -e 'print "set_time ", time(), "\n"'; echo time) | telnet xx.xx.xx.xx 40000

Parameters:
S console session
Out where to write any output

00811 {
00812     Exporter *E = (Exporter *) Arg;
00813     IPDR_Time newTime;
00814     IPDR_Status Status;
00815     char newTimeStr[IPDR_TIME_FORMAT_LENGTH+1];
00816     if (Argc != 1) {
00817         Console_Println(S, Out, "set_time: Invalid number of arguments");
00818         return IPDR_OK;
00819     }
00820     newTime = atoi(Argv[0]);
00821     Platform_FormatTimeLocal(E->PS, newTime, newTimeStr);
00822     Status = Platform_SetTime(E->PS, newTime);
00823     if (SUCCESS(Status)) {
00824         Console_Println(S, Out, "Time set to %lu (%.60s)", newTime, newTimeStr);
00825         /* Output a warning level message because this time change
00826          * could cause some things to misbehave. */
00827         Log_OutputStr2(&E->ExporterLog, EXPORTER_MODULE_ID, IPDR_LEVEL_WARNING, "ExporterConsole",
00828                        "Time set to %lu (%.60s)", newTime, newTimeStr);
00829     } else {
00830         char msg[IPDR_MAX_ERROR_LENGTH+1];
00831         Platform_GetLastErrorMessage(E->PS, msg);
00832         Log_OutputStr3(&E->ExporterLog, EXPORTER_MODULE_ID, IPDR_LEVEL_ERROR, "ExporterConsole",
00833                        "Failed time set to %lu (%.60s): %.100s", newTime, newTimeStr, msg);
00834         Console_Println(S, Out, "Could not set time to %lu (%.60s): %.100s",
00835                         newTime, newTimeStr, msg);
00836     }
00837     return IPDR_OK;
00838 }
